# CLI changes and validation

When you **change or validate CLI functionality** (especially when the CLI is consumed by another repo), **always use the cli-qa-release subagent**. It covers: publish RC → verify in consumer → (when ready) revert pins to latest, bump version, commit, push, tag; GitHub Actions publish to npm; verify on registry. Do not stop at "publish an RC and try it"—run the full cycle through verification (and release when the user wants to cut stable).

**Publish auth:** NPM_TOKEN is in AWS Secrets Manager secret `devops`. Write `.npmrc.publish` with `//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=<token>`, run `npm publish ... --userconfig .npmrc.publish`. Add `.npmrc.publish` to `.gitignore` and leave it locally. See `cursor-config/skills/cli-qa-release/SKILL.md` for the one-liner and release steps.
